Preprocessing / feature engineering

Taking a look at our preprocessed training data Since there usually is less Fail in a program, will use upsampling to increase this number so that we can assess our training model better As you can see now we have 5 fails and 5 pass

Preparing our cross validation (model validation dataset) (k=5, repeats =5)

## #  5-fold cross-validation repeated 5 times using stratification 
## # A tibble: 25 x 3
##    splits        id      id2  
##    <list>        <chr>   <chr>
##  1 <split [5/2]> Repeat1 Fold1
##  2 <split [5/2]> Repeat1 Fold2
##  3 <split [6/1]> Repeat1 Fold3
##  4 <split [6/1]> Repeat1 Fold4
##  5 <split [6/1]> Repeat1 Fold5
##  6 <split [5/2]> Repeat2 Fold1
##  7 <split [5/2]> Repeat2 Fold2
##  8 <split [6/1]> Repeat2 Fold3
##  9 <split [6/1]> Repeat2 Fold4
## 10 <split [6/1]> Repeat2 Fold5
## # ... with 15 more rows

What this does is it uses our training set, group our training dataset 5 different times and uses 1 set as a test set. Then repeat 5 more times.

Finalize our model and assess with test set

set.seed(1)
final_wf <- workflow() %>%
  add_recipe(ite2_recipe) %>%
  add_model(rftuneres)

finalres <- final_wf %>%
  last_fit(split)

finalres %>%
  collect_predictions() %>%
  conf_mat(Pass, .pred_class)
##           Truth
## Prediction No Yes
##        No   0   1
##        Yes  1   1
finalres %>%
  collect_metrics() %>%
  datatable()
final_model <- fit(final_wf, ite2)
final_model
